# Silicon Labs Project Configuration Tools: slcp, v0, Component selection file.
project_name: iostream_usart_baremetal
label: iostream_usart_baremetal
description: |
  This application demonstrates how to use the I/O Stream service in a bare-metal configuration to enable UART communication over a virtual COM port (VCOM).  It will echo back any characters received through the serial connection, and the VCOM serial port operates over USB, allowing for communication between the device and a host.  This setup showcases basic serial communication using UART.
category: example|peripheral
package: platform
quality: production
